19/03/2006
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- During talks in Podgorica on Saturday (18 March), Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic and his Macedonian counterpart, Vlado Buckovski, called for greater regional co-operation. They agreed that promoting a spirit of stability and solidarity is crucial this year, given a series of key regional developments. These include Montenegro's independence referendum process, the constitutional reform process in BiH and the determination of Kosovo's final status. (Telma TV, Makfax - 18/03/06)
